race.comment: VERBIL (5) was hard to fault in the first three runs this prep then the form dipped last start when a distant third over 1300m at Randwick. Steps up to this distance for the first time but he gives every indication he will run it out. Big chance back in midweek company on a firmer track. NAILS MURPHY (1) improved nicely last time out at the second run of the campaign, making late ground to grab second over 1500m at Rosehill. Handled the wet okay that day which isn't always the case so he is going well. Drops in grade and should be close to his peak. DEBELLO (3) led for the judge then battled on fairly to finish sixth in the rich Four Pillars over 1500m at Randwick recently. Likes Canterbury and will enjoy the run of the race out of the inside stall. ZENMASTER (7) tends to mix his form. Cherry ripe after three runs back and is a winner here at the trip.
